name: polar-amino-acid-transporting ATPase
classes: Acting on acid anhydrides to catalyse transmembrane movement of substances
reaction: ATP + H2O + polar amino acidout = ADP + phosphate + polar amino acidin [RN:R00086]
comment: ABC-type (ATP-binding cassette-type) ATPase, characterized by the presence of two similar ATP-binding domains. Does not undergo phosphorylation during the transport process. Comprises bacterial enzymes that import His, Arg, Lys, Glu, Gln, Asp, ornithine, octopine and nopaline.

orthologs.K02028: polar amino acid transport system ATP-binding protein

references.title: Phylogenetic analyses of the ATP-binding constituents of bacterial extracytoplasmic receptor-dependent ABC-type nutrient uptake permeases.
Molecular phylogeny as a basis for the classification of transport proteins from bacteria, archaea and eukarya.

Purification and characterization of HisP, the ATP-binding subunit of a traffic ATPase (ABC transporter), the histidine permease of Salmonella typhimurium. Solubility, dimerization, and ATPase activity.
Distribution of a sub-class of bacterial ABC polar amino acid transporter and identification of an N-terminal region involved in solute specificity.
